---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import pages from '../data/pages.json';
import siteData from '../data/site.json';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${pages.about.title} | ${siteData.siteDefaults.title}`}
  description={pages.about.description}
>
  <article class="about">
    <h1 class="about__title">{pages.about.title}</h1>
    <div class="about__body">
      <p>
        r3frag is a static archive of short scientific, artistic, and threaded fragments. It holds
        a single chronological stream so the record remains visible, even when the song changes.
        Not every fragment resolves into a system. Some are simply what I can see at the time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Science fragments are working notes &mdash; questions I&rsquo;m holding, assumptions under
        scrutiny, implications I&rsquo;m tracing. Art fragments are images or brief lines, moments
        rendered without explanation. Thread fragments trace recurrence, relationship, and the
        quiet logic between things. The archive is intentionally small, built to last, and quiet
        enough to return to.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
